Package smProject3

Class Date

  • java.lang.Object
    • smProject3.Date
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Date>
    public class Date
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Date>
    Contains information about a single date. This includes the month, day of month, and year. Can determine if the date is a valid calendar date. This is the same Date class from project 1.
    Author:
    Aaron Browne, Harshkumar Patel

      • isValid

        public boolean isValid()
        Determines whether or not the date is a valid calendar date. Does not allow years before 1900 or after the current one. Takes into account the amount of days of different months and leap years.
        Returns:
        true if the date is valid, false if not.
